data.title: Battle of Quingua
data.meta_description: Battle-of-Quingua.docx - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. 1) The Battle of Quingua Monument commemorates the battle that occurred on April 23, 1899 in Quingua, now Plaridel, Bulacan during the Philippine-American War. 2) In the battle, the American forces led by Major J. Franklin Bell were initially stopped by Filipino forces led by General Gregorio del Pilar. However, the Filipinos were eventually routed after Colonel John M. Stotsenburg and the 1st Nebraska Volunteer Infantry Regiment reinforced the Americans. 3) Colonel Stotsenburg was killed during the battle, making him the highest ranking American casualty of the war up to that point.
